sources.title: Out West
sources.description: Out West (1918) A Fatty Arbuckle comedy including performances by Buster Keaton and Al St John. It is a parody of Western pictures of the way.

sources.title: OUT WEST (1918) -- Roscoe Arbuckle, Buster Keaton, Al St. John
sources.description: OUT WEST (1918) Starring: Roscoe Arbuckle, Buster Keaton, Al St. John, Alice Lake Written by Natalie Talmadge Photographed by George Peters Directed by Arbuckle Produced by Joseph M. Schenck Paramount Wm. Thomas Sherman, wts@gunjones.com, http://www.mn-hp.com

metadata.Plot: A satire of western movies. Roscoe comes into town after riding the rails. The saloon has a trap door over a pit where bodies are tossed as they are shot. A black patron is taunted and shot at. Roscoe and Buster do everything they can to keep Al from Alice.
metadata.Actors: Roscoe 'Fatty' Arbuckle, Buster Keaton, Al St. John
